main event: An unidentified flying object was detected on radar at Larson AFB, Washington on 26 August 1951.
interesting points: The object was tracked for about 5 to 6 minutes,The radar operator estimated the object was traveling at speeds of 900 to 1,000 mph,The F-86 aircraft were scrambled but radar contact with the object was lost,The object was first tracked between 17,000 to 20,000 feet before descending rapidly,Review concluded the radar return was positive, meaning the object was real.
sighted object: unidentified flying object detected on radar
witness description: Air Force radar operator experienced in radar operations
